storyInfo: A wounded Skadi comes to an Iberian village. Its people fervently accept her, but she's begun to doubt herself...

attributes.text: Skadi does not recall how far she's walked.
She only knows that so long as what lies beneath her feet is solid earth, she does not belong here.
But she can only walk upon the land.
The land. 'Tierra.' The first Iberian word she learned.

attributes.content: Who's Rober?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Ah, that's me.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: This is your food for today.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Ah, alright.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: Also, Joni wanted me to bring this present to you.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Oh, these are my favorite flowers! Why didn't he come himself?
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: He said he was working.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Coward.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: If you're fine, I'm going.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Hey, hey, visitor, wait.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: He already paid.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: No, you're Skadi, the bounty hunter who came into the village recently, right?
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: Mm.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: I hear you've been doing a lot for us. I've been wanting to meet you.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: It wasn't anything major.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Sit down, Skadi. Eat something, it's on me.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: ...Is there wine?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Will ale be okay?
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: Mm.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Here.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: Your accent's very strange, Skadi. You're not an Iberian, are you?
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: Mm.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: How rare. We often have refugees pass through this place, but I've never seen someone who wasn't an Iberian before.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: Visitor, where did you come from?
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: I came from the sea.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: The sea? You’re an Ægir?
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: We have Ægir in our village too, but I don't think they're too different from us. Not like you. I felt the difference between us the moment I saw you.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: I've heard them tell of how they all left Ægir and came ashore when my grandfather was my age.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: Oh, yes. My neighbor is an Ægir too. I'll get her to have a chat with you.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: No need.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: She once held such hopes, but when she saw the Ægir of dry land, she knew she and they were nothing alike.
Only the oldest of them still dimly remembered what Ægir even looked like.
She had nothing she could share with them, nor they with her.
Alright.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: Ah, Skadi, did you know? The village has been talking about you every day.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: Hm?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: When you arrived in the village, you gave everyone an awful scare. We all thought you were just fleeing here after other bounty hunters injured you.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: It frightened us. A wounded bounty hunter is like a temperamental beast.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: Most creatures of dry land are frail, unable to harm her.
What harmed her were those who profess themselves the Church of the Deep.
They were fixated on her for reasons unknown. Moreover, they were clearly unlike ordinary Iberians.
But now, they're all saying they've never met a bounty hunter as kind as you.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: Are bounty hunters usually bad news?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: We've had bounty hunters hiding in our village before. They were especially ferocious, and kept clashing with the villagers.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: So at first, we'd all discussed whether or not to drive you away.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: I'll leave.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Don't! You've given us so much help these past few days. We're all so fond of you now.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: You can stay here as long as you like.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: Or is there someplace you need to go?
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.text: Is there someplace I must go?

attributes.content: I don't know.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Really? Then are you going back home?
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: Ah, I'm sorry. I know, I know, there're so many people who run far away because their homes have been destroyed. I'm so stupid...
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: No.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Eh?
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: No, maybe you're right.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Oh! The bell's ringing?
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: What's happening?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: The village's bell only sounds in times of emergency...
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: Rober, Rober!
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: Joni, weren't you working?
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: Hide yourself!
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: What's going on?!
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: There's a pack of monsters near the village! They've hurt some of us already! We need to hold them off!
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: Get down to the cellar and hide, now!
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: O-Okay!
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: Skadi, you... you're not one of us. You'd better run.
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: If you're scared, come with me. Our house's cellar can hide plenty of people.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: Since coming ashore, Skadi has had a constant feeling.
This feeling gradually grows ever stronger in the wake of these occurrences. Violent, relentless, restless.
But she has never dared convince herself.
She dares not convince herself— that she is why the sea monsters come.
Eek! Noooo!!!
attributes.name: Terrified Villager

attributes.content: Quick, hide behind me!
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: Wh—What are these monsters?!
attributes.name: Terrified Villager

attributes.content: I've heard tales! They're monsters from the sea!
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: Normally, they'd never crawl out to a dry inland place like this. Why would they show here...?
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: And so many!
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: What now?! It doesn't look hurt at all!
attributes.name: Terrified Villager

attributes.content: ...They don't move that fast. Run, meet with the others!
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: Okay...
attributes.name: Terrified Villager

attributes.content: Eek! They're here too!
attributes.name: Terrified Villager

attributes.content: No! Stay back!
attributes.name: Terrified Villager

attributes.content: Damn things! I'll take you with me!
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: Guh...
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: No! Nooo!
attributes.name: Terrified Villager

attributes.content: With just a single sword... Skadi, you're so strong!
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: Are you going to stay and help us?
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: Mm.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You really are a good one!
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: I'm not.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: ...Come with me.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: When Skadi opened her eyes on the beach, she found not a single soul by her side.
Ægir. Abyssal Hunters. All lives on the line, flesh to flesh, blood to blood.
None of it seemed to exist.
Only the sounds of the waves and the wind stirred in her ears.
Countless times she tried to return to the ocean.
But every time, countless sea monsters would surround her, forcing her to turn back midway.
Out of the way.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: At some point, as she was forced yet again to swim back, she even felt a sort of misperception arise within her—
That the abyssal infinitude of monsters were not pursuing her, but rather sending her off.
(Ægirian) Why—must you come near me?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Once she became aware of the possibility she may never return to the sea, she had no choice but to turn around on the shore and set foot onto this land she'd never been concerned with before.
This land.
Skadi's incredible...
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: Rober, what are you doing out here?!
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: I was worried for Skadi... and besides, she's come to help us. Shouldn't we at least help defend our own homes?
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: You're right...
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: Absolutely right!
attributes.name: Brave Villager

attributes.content: I don't need help.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: In her eyes, the people of dry land are by and large akin to the ones before her now.
Frail, melancholic, leading lives devoid of efficiency or any positive qualities to speak of.
Don't be like that, Skadi. We can't let you bear everything for us.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: I'll go and help her! I don't know if I can hurt any of these monsters, but I can at least distract some of them!
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: I'll help too!
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: Everyone, with Skadi!
attributes.name: Brave Villager

attributes.content: (Ægirian) I said—don't come near me!
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: But she is forced to admit. There are some points of intersection between them, where they can understand one another. In the emotional.
She can understand what circumstances lead them to feel what sentiments.
And it is exactly this that vexes her more and more. It is for this that she feels guilt.
But she cannot divulge these feelings to the villagers. She can only hasten the swing of the greatsword in her hand.
What's she saying?
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: Look, she's moving faster! I'm sure she's encouraging us!
attributes.name: Brave Villager

attributes.content: Alright, watch this!
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: Get out of my sight, monsters!
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: Rgh...
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: Don't be scared! See how you like THIS, monster!
attributes.name: Brave Villager

attributes.content: Appreciated!
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: We're all friends. It's only right.
attributes.name: Brave Villager

attributes.content: They're scared! Keep going, everyone, let's drive these monsters out!
attributes.name: Brave Villager

attributes.content: Yeah!
attributes.name: Villagers

attributes.content: Wonderful! I think the rest have run. I can't see any trace of them around the village anymore.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: Heh heh. We're pretty incredible ourselves, aren't we?
attributes.name: Brave Villager

attributes.content: What are you so proud of? If it wasn't for Skadi, we'd probably all be done for.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: Hahah, just leave him be. We all made it through, so let him have this one.
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: Alright, alright.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: She too once had comrades-in-arms, ones who fought alongside her, shared in the revelry of battle with her.
A vast number of them perished in that battle.
In the past, she was no stranger to sacrifice.
But as she watches the villagers share in the joy from the bottoms of their hearts, a thought suddenly comes to her—
She may be the very last Abyssal Hunter.
What's wrong, Skadi? You don't look happy.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: ...It's nothing.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: If you ask me, I bet she's hungry.
attributes.name: Brave Villager

attributes.content: Now that you mention it, I'm a little hungry too, haha!
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.content: Enough of that. Still, Skadi, you saved the day today. I'll personally prepare a feast in honor of you tonight.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: And I'm sure nobody in the village is opposed to you becoming one of us, after you helped us in such a tremendous way.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: I was never opposed from the start!
attributes.name: Brave Villager

attributes.content: No objections from me either! Hear hear, Skadi, stay in our village as long as you like, I say!
attributes.name: Panicky Villager

attributes.text: To you, the battle just now hardly registered as a warmup.
But to a village as weak as this, those monsters could easily have been the wave that drowns them.

attributes.content: It's true, Skadi. With your might, we'd also feel so much safer if you stayed.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.text: You don't belong here. You'll bring ruin to this place.

attributes.content: Don't you have nowhere to go?
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: You can live with us.
attributes.name: Friendly Villager

attributes.content: No. I've decided now.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: If I can't return to the sea, then I'll go where there's no water.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Hey, you hear about that Skadi business?
attributes.name: Chatty Bounty Hunter

attributes.content: Skadi? Don't think I have.
attributes.name: Curious Bounty Hunter

attributes.content: Something tells me your grapevine sucks.
attributes.name: Chatty Bounty Hunter

attributes.content: Fine, fine, I'm out of the loop, just tell me already.
attributes.name: Curious Bounty Hunter

attributes.content: Skadi's this Ægir who suddenly showed up out of nowhere a little while ago.
attributes.name: Chatty Bounty Hunter

attributes.content: Ægir? Where's that from?
attributes.name: Curious Bounty Hunter

attributes.content: You... whatever. Makes sense a Kazimierzian would never hear about Ægir. I don't know too much myself, but I know it's a country and that's enough.
attributes.name: Chatty Bounty Hunter

attributes.content: Ohh... and? What's up with this Skadi?
attributes.name: Curious Bounty Hunter

attributes.content: She's got this giant greatsword, and you wouldn't miss her clothes from a mile away, but she's refused to ever work with anyone else. At first, everyone thought she'd kick it in the middle of nowhere.
attributes.name: Chatty Bounty Hunter

attributes.content: But she's not only been thriving, she's been stealing a lot of other people's work.
attributes.name: Chatty Bounty Hunter

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Curious Bounty Hunter

attributes.content: Last month, 'Flamelung' announced he was going to sort her out. Guess what happened?
attributes.name: Chatty Bounty Hunter

attributes.content: He drove her off?
attributes.name: Curious Bounty Hunter

attributes.content: No, she took down the entire squad he sent at her!
attributes.name: Chatty Bounty Hunter

attributes.content: That's... Where the hell did she come from?
attributes.name: Curious Bounty Hunter

attributes.content: Don't know. Got sources who say she showed up alongside a bunch of bounty hunters coming back from Iberia.
attributes.name: Chatty Bounty Hunter

attributes.content: Either way, apparently it's got 'Flamelung' pretty goddamn fuming now. Me, I'm looking forward to the show.
attributes.name: Chatty Bounty Hunter

attributes.content: Excuse me.
attributes.name: Taciturn Passerby

attributes.content: Huh? Who're you?
attributes.name: Chatty Bounty Hunter

attributes.content: Who I am does not matter, I'm simply curious. You just mentioned an Ægir. Where is she right now?
attributes.name: Taciturn Passerby
